6 6–302.
7 (a) Except as otherwise provided in this section and after complying with § 6–305
8 of this subtitle, in each year after the date of finality and before the following July 1, the
9 Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or the governing body of each county annually
10 shall set the tax rate for the next taxable year on all assessments of property subject to that
11 county’s property tax.
12 (b) (1) Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section and §§ 6–305 and
13 6–306 of this subtitle:
14 (i) there shall be a single county property tax rate for all real
15 property subject to county property tax except for operating real property described in §
16 8–109(c) of this article; and
17 (ii) the county tax rate applicable to personal property and the
18 operating real property described in § 8–109(c) of this article shall be no more than 2.5
19 times the rate for real property.
20 (2) Paragraph (1) of this subsection does not affect a special rate prevailing
21 in a taxing district or part of a county.
22 (c) (1) The Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or the governing body of
23 a county may set a special rate for a vacant lot or improved property cited as vacant and
24 unfit for habitation or other authorized use on a housing or building violation notice.
25 (2) (I) IN THIS PARAGRAPH, “COUNTY TAX LIMITATION” HAS THE
26 MEANING STATED IN § 21–701 OF THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
27 (II) THIS PARAGRAPH APPLIES ONLY IN PRINCE GEORGE’S
28 COUNTY.
29 (III) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, A
30 COUNTY TAX LIMITATION DOES NOT APPLY TO A PROPERTY TAX RATE SET BY THE
31 GOVERNING BODY OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY IN THE EXERCISE OF THE
32 AUTHORITY GRANTED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.

